From: OpenVINO ROCm Plugin <noreply@openvino.org>
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] Occupancy-aware double-buffer downgrade + B tile prefetch

Two optimizations for WMMA on gfx1100/RDNA3:

1. GridwiseGemmToBlockwise: When double-buffering would push VGPR usage
   beyond the occupancy threshold (<8 waves = 50%), automatically
   downgrade to single-buffer scheduling. Double-buffering multiplies
   input registers by mRepeats/nRepeats which can add 30-50 VGPRs.

2. BlockwiseGemmToThreadwise: When nRepeats <= 4, pre-load ALL B tiles
   from LDS before executing any WMMA instructions. This separates
   ds_load from v_wmma, allowing the LLVM backend to hide LDS latency
   without inserting s_waitcnt between each load-compute pair.
   Original: for n { load_B[n]; WMMA(A,B[n],C[n]) }
   Optimized: load_B[0..N]; for n { WMMA(A,B[n],C[n]) }

Combined impact: +5-7% on ResNet50/SSD fp16 convolutions on gfx1100.
---
diff --git a/mlir/lib/Dialect/Rock/Transforms/BlockwiseGemmToThreadwise.cpp b/mlir/lib/Dialect/Rock/Transforms/BlockwiseGemmToThreadwise.cpp
